node.text:
.
.
.
Ingredients:
8 oz lump crab
1/2 cup almond flour
1 large egg
1/4 cup chopped parsley 
1 tbsp fresh minced garlic
1 tbsp Mayo
1 tbsp Dijon mustard
1/2 tsp salt
1/2 tsp thyme 
1/8 tsp cayenne pepper
.
.
Instructions:
1. Whisk egg & mix with all ingredients. Shape into patties and let refrigerate on wax paper for 1 hour.
2. Pan fry in butter or oil of choice until golden brown on both sides. Let cool & enjoy!
.
.
#keto #lowcarb #ketorecipes

node.text:
.
.
.
Ingredients:
1 lb strawberries sliced
1.5 cups sweetener
2 tbsp lemon juice
.
.
Instructions:
1. Add your strawberries to a sauce pan on medium heat and mix in the sugar. 
2. Stir until you bring the strawberries to a boil.
3. Once boiling add your lemon juice. 
4. Let boil for another 15 minutes / until jam reaches 220F stirring often so the jam doesn’t burn. 
5. Pour into a jar and let cool. 
.
.
#keto #ketorecipes #lowcarb #strawberries

node.text:
.
.
.
The Ellas Flats are such a bussin keto friendly option when you’re craving something light & crunchy 🙌 I highly reccomend you go order some! The link is in my bio 👍
.
.
Ingredients:
1/4 cup allulose 
2 TBSP butter
4-5 Ellas flats (link in bio)
1 tsp vanilla extract
1/8 tsp salt
.
.
Instructions:
1. Combine all ingredients except the flats in a non stick skillet over medium heat until the sweetener dissolves.
2. Add Flats and stir for 2-3 minutes.
3. Remove from stove and pour into a rimmed baking sheet / Pan lined with parchment paper. Spread peanuts evenly with a spoon. (Be careful it’s very hot)
4. Allow to cool for 1 hour. Break up into 4 servings and enjoy!
.
.
#keto #lowcarb #ketosnacks #ketotreats #ellasflats

node.text:
Leave a “🥩🥩🥩” if you will NEVER stop eating meat! 💪 

Reminder: MEAT, EGGS & FATTY FISH ARE SUPER FOODS!

Most studies that show meat to be harmful were not measuring the health of people who eat steak and avocados for dinner, they were looking at people who eat cheeseburgers with soda and fries (that were probably cooked in inflammatory oils).

If you’re vegan for moral reasons, that’s amazing and I totally support your decision! However; it doesn’t change the fact that it is difficult to get essential nutrients like Vitamins A & B, Zinc, Iron, etc.. without animal products. It’s also hard to get the Omega-3 Fatty Acids that your body actually uses (EPA & DHA) without consuming animal products or fish oil. You can get plant based omega-3’s in the form of ALA but your body loses around 90% of them when converting them to EPA & DHA which means you have to consume 10x as much for the same benefit 😱

I’m also aware that Keto has become a bit cultish in similar ways to veganism. However, most researchers who support Keto are dedicated to optimizing the health of HUAMNS. Whereas most vegan activists who make documentaries like What the Health are on a mission to save animals, which makes their claims about “human health” feel less credible to me. No disrespect though, just don’t tell me what to eat and I won’t tell you what to eat! ❤️

#carnivore #keto #lowcarb #paleo

node.text:
BREAKFAST QUESADILLA 🍳🥓🧀 What would you dip this in? 😋 

Ingredients:
Butter
Low carb tortilla
Shredded cheese
Eggs 
Bacon
Seasonings of your choice

Instructions:
1. Coat your tortilla in melted butter & add your fillings. (make sure cheese is on both sides of the fillings so it sticks)
2. Pan fry until both sides are crispy. 
3. Remove from pan, let cool, & enjoy!

Pro tip: The heat from frying the quesadilla will cook your eggs a bit, so I use slightly undercooked eggs when I make mine 👍

#keto #lowcarb #ketorecipes #breakfast

.

1/2 cup shredded cheddar
Seasonings of your choice
.
.

.
.

Say “YES” if you would eat these Crispy Brussels Sprouts 😋

Leave a “🤢” if you hate Brussels sprouts!!
